# Integration tests

Mocha + earl + ts-rest client. Tests run against a Dockerized stack (`test/setup/test-app.docker-compose.yml`).

## Rules

- Assert via `@total-report/core-contract` types/clients — not `core-service` internals.
- Seed data with `@total-report/core-entities-generator`; add factories there when needed.
- Auth: `loginVerifiedTestUser()` from `test/tools/auth.ts` (creates verified user, returns `client` + `generator`).
- Clients: `publicClient` / `authenticatedClient(token)` in `test/tools/client.ts`.
- Earl extensions: `test/tools/earl-extensions.js`; helpers in `test/tools/utils.ts`.
- Hooks: `test/setup/hooks.ts` starts/stops Docker (`test:app:up` / `test:app:down`).

## Test file pattern

```typescript
let client: VerifiedTestUserSession["client"];
let generator: CoreEntititesGenerator;

before(async () => {
  ({ client, generator } = await loginVerifiedTestUser());
});

test("...", async () => {
  const launch = await generator.launches.create();
  const response = await client.createTest({ body: { ... } });
  expect(response).toEqual({ status: 201, headers: expect.anything(), body: { ... } });
});
```

- Mirror contract request types: `ClientInferRequest<typeof contract.createTest>`.
- Env: `test/setup/test.env` (port `3334`, DB on `5433`).
